thread.title: Jamall Shaw rushes for 189 yards, three TDs as Broken Arrow rolls over Westmoore
thread.title_full: Jamall Shaw rushes for 189 yards, three TDs as Broken Arrow rolls over Westmoore

title: Jamall Shaw rushes for 189 yards, three TDs as Broken Arrow rolls over Westmoore
text:
Sponsored Links By Duane Dapron, Broken Arrow Ledger 
With district races starting to take shape, Class 6A-I No. 3 Broken Arrow appears to be in full stride. 
With Jamall Shaw rushing for 189 yards and three touchdowns and a defense getting three takeaways to help set up short scoring drives, the Tigers tallied their fourth straight District 6AI-1 blowout by rolling past No. 8 Westmoore 45-6 on Thursday night at Memorial Stadium. 
The victory by Broken Arrow (6-1, 4-0), which has outscored its four District 6AI-1 opponents this season 234-34, sets up a battle for the district’s top spot next week when the Tigers play at defending Class 6AI champ and No. 1-ranked Jenks. 
“Jenks hasn’t lost at home since about 2006 but I am looking forward to taking this group there,” Broken Arrow coach David Alexander said. “We’ll go there and take our best swing and see what happens.” Sign up for our FOX23 News This Morning Newsletter Sign Up
